February 17, 2026
ENGROSSED
HOUSE BILL No. 1055
_____
DIGEST OF HB 1055 (Updated February 16, 2026 12:05 pm - DI 149)
Citations Affected: IC 3-5; IC 3-6; IC 3-8; IC 3-10; IC 3-11; IC 3-12;
IC 3-13; IC 5-4; IC 33-35; IC 36-1; IC 36-1.5; IC 36-3; IC 36-4;
IC 36-5; noncode.
Synopsis: Municipal elections. Moves, as a general rule, elections of
town officers to even-numbered years. Allows a town with a population
of more than 10,000 to opt out of the general rule by resolution. Allows
a city to pass a resolution to opt in to the general rule. Makes
conforming changes.
Effective: Upon passage; July 1, 2026.
Meltzer, Zimmerman, Lawson,
Bascom
(SENATE SPONSOR — KOCH)
